<plm2@cornell.edu>
[The methodology ... MLVA "Multi-locus variable number tandem repeat"
is given in Keim et al, J Bact 2000 vol 182(10): 2928-2936. It works
by measuring the number of repeats at various places in the gene
sequence. These repeat areas have been mapped and we know the range of
possible repeats for each. Essentially, it is a bar-code.
While Sterne and Ames are in the same genetype group ("Sterne-Ames")
there are significant differences. We have located wild Sterne in
Africa with all its plasmids. The Ames could have come from virtually
anywhere, as the classic cultivar was circulated widely. However we
have only found wild versions of Ames in the USA. - Mods.MHJ/TG]
[Many veterinarians accidentally inoculate themselves with vaccine
strains -- livestock doesn´t stand still for the needle. Results vary
from nothing at all to easily treated skin lesions. - Mod.JW]
..........................................................mhj/tg/pg/jw
